The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for paraphrase identification, which are typically studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of shared URLs from Twitter to collect paraphrase data also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and social media analysis (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the utility of the paraphrase dataset for downstream NLP tasks, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
